CONGRATULATIONS Corporal Nidhi Sah from K.C. Das Commerce College represented the 1 Assam Battalion, NCC, under the Guwahati Group of the North Eastern Region Directorate at the prestigious Ek Bharat Shreshtha Bharat (EBSB) Camp held in Agartala, Tripura, from 16th to 27th December 2024.

During the camp, she actively participated in various events, securing medals in Nukkad Natak (street play), group dance, and tug of war, making her the highest medal winner from the Guwahati Group.

Cpl Nidhi Sah was also selected as part of Team 10, a group of cadets who had the honor of interacting with Lieutenant General Vikas Lakhera, AVSM, VSM, the Director General of Assam Rifles.

Beyond the competitive events, she visited several significant sites in Tripura, including the Ujjayanta Palace, Neermahal,Tripura Sundari Temple, Heritage Park,war memorials , and the India-Bangladesh border, enriching her understanding of the region’s cultural and historical heritage.

Her exemplary participation and achievements at the EBSB Camp 2024 highlight her dedication, talent, and the spirit of unity that the National Cadet Corps strives to instill in its cadets.
